## Example 7 (Congruence)

a) Congruence under endomorphisms

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i, F:$i>$i]: (
    (X = Y) => (F @ X = F @ Y)
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
thf(leibniz_t, type, l: A > A > $o).
thf(leibniz_def, definition,
  l = ^[X, Y]: ![P]: P @ X => P @ Y
).
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i, F:$i>$i]: (
    (l @ X @ Y) => (l @ (F @ X) @ (F @ Y))
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{leibniz2}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i, F:$i>$i]: (
    (l @ X @ Y) => (l @ (F @ X) @ (F @ Y))
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{leibniz3}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i, F:$i>$i]: (
    (l @ X @ Y) => (l @ (F @ X) @ (F @ Y))
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# Timeout
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{andrews}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i, Y:$i, F:$i>$i]: (
    (a @ X @ Y) => (a @ (F @ X) @ (F @ Y))
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{extensional}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![X:$i>$i, Y:$i>$i, F:($i>$i)>$i>$i]: (
    (e @ X @ Y) => (e @ (F @ X) @ (F @ Y))
  )
).
"""

format_result res
# Timeout
```

