## Example 9 (Trivial Directions of Extensionality)

a) Functional Extensionality

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>$i, G:$i>$i]: ( (F = G) => (![X:$i]: F @ X = G @ X) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{leibniz1}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>$i, G:$i>$i]: ( (l @ F @ G) => (![X:$i]: (l @ (F @ X) @ (G @ X))) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{leibniz2}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>$i, G:$i>$i]: ( (l @ F @ G) => (![X:$i]: l @ (F @ X) @ (G @ X)) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{leibniz3}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>$i, G:$i>$i]: ( (l @ F @ G) => (![X:$i]: l @ (F @ X) @ (G @ X)) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{andrews}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>$i, G:$i>$i]: ( (a @ F @ G) => (![X:$i]: a @ (F @ X) @ (G @ X)) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

```elixir
res = prove ~p"""
#{extensional}
thf(conj, conjecture,
  ![F:$i>($i>$i), G:$i>($i>$i)]: ( (e @ F @ G) => (![X:$i]: e @ (F @ X) @ (G @ X)) )
).
"""

format_result res
# THM
```

b) Boolean Extensionality

```elixir
